contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"An animated gif shows Naked Snake switching ammo with an in-game menu option.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eGif: Konami / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"d79aee933c8d455936aa4e6da99e4f40\" data-recommend-id=\"image://d79aee933c8d455936aa4e6da99e4f40\" data-format=\"gif\" data-width=\"800\" data-height=\"450\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"An animated gif shows Naked Snake switching ammo with an in-game menu option.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eI’m just gonna level with ya’ll, I didn’t think much of \u003cem\u003eMetal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater\u003c/em\u003e in 2004. But a new look at an improved gameplay feature in the upcoming remake, \u003cem\u003eMetal Gear Solid Delta\u003c/em\u003e, might just be enough to convert this jaded fan who’s convinced the series peaked at \u003cem\u003eSons of Liberty\u003c/em\u003e. In a 12-second clip, Naked Snake can be seen swapping his camo from a foresty look to something more suitable for an urban environment in record time. It’s way faster and less cumbersome-looking than the camo-swapping of the original.  - Claire Jackson \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/metal-gear-solid-3-snake-eater-camo-feature-new-1851772814\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/metal-gear-solid-3-snake-eater-camo-feature-new-1851772814\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
